fsjTxL9kGb3p.title: Cordova
fsjTxL9kGb3p.content:
Cordova is a hamlet in the Artemisian Tundra.

The settlement is located in a valley on the north side of the Avens Reservoir, along the bank of River Avens. It's the northernmost settlement in Artemisia, and in Rostock.

History and formation

The town of Cordova is the result of excavation and mining projects organised by the Rostock Guild of Metallurgy, who paid for a permanent settlement to be constructed in the tundra to be used as a base of operations for nearby mines and quarries in the materially prosperous Artemisian Tundra. Settlers and the tools they'd need for construction were transported out to the Tundra by ox-drawn caravans in the summer when travel was easiest, and after minimal scouting it was determined that settling by the natural reservoir would be optimal. Permanent structures consisting of housing, a small mill and a public house, were constructed utilizing stone from a nearby quarry and as little wood as possible from their transported materials.

Cairns were constructed to mark the path from Cordova to the Northern Chauntean Monastery, which is the nearest settlement.

Culture & Population

Cordova has a population of 53, none of which are children. The population is ‘curated’ by the Rostock Guild of Metallurgy, since they can pick and choose who they send and sponsor to live in the hamlet

While Cordova is situated in a hostile environment, the residents may find these living conditions preferable to the housing in large cities or small towns. Both of those options carry their own dangers and discomforts, whereas the guild who sponsors this settlement provides for all it's needs. Food is transported to the hamlet via a monthly caravan because they can't cultivate crops easily in the tundra, and protection from animals and monsters is provided by guild-funded mercenaries. Supplies are delivered to the publican, who in-turn hands them out evenly to the population.

CqZrfAuwcy2C.title: Lake Avens
CqZrfAuwcy2C.content:
Lake Avens is a natural reservoir formed at the end of a u-shaped valley in the Artemisian Tundra. It's fed into by River Avens, which flows down the valley and collects in the basin. The water in Lake Avens is clean freshwater, and so it's used as a source of drinking water for the nearby settlement Cordova.

Being located in the Artemisian Tundra, Lake Avens is completely frozen over for roughly a quarter of each year in the winter. After a month of thawing it returns to being flat and clear, however small chunks of ice still sometimes form. The lake is also home to a small population of fish, mainly arctic char.

39ALIal8QixK.title: River Avens
39ALIal8QixK.content:
River Avens is a brook that forms in the Artemisian Tundra and runs down into southern Rostock. By definition, River Avens is not wide enough to be classified as a river, however it's already been marked as such on maps of Rostock and Artemisia. The river collects in Lake Avens before continuing down into southern Rostock, passing through Glyndale and flowing into the sea.

River Avens does not have a single source, instead it's fed by many tributaries which are each sourced by melting snow and ice runoff on the mountains surrounding the u-shaped valley in which it's head is situated. These tributaries flow down the valley from either side and meet in the center, forming the brook.

4XLQvSOCploT.title: Northern Chauntean Monastery
4XLQvSOCploT.content:
The Northern Chauntean Monastery is an old religious site in the Artemisian Highlands which has been repurposed as a monastery by the Chauntean church in Glyndale. It acts as a mid-way point for travel and transport between Glyndale and Cordova.

tC1BjDva4PbD.title: Nariin Alakh
tC1BjDva4PbD.content:
The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

"Nariin Alakh is a confident and fair Prince of the Ledus Rus. A skilled warrior and an advocate for continental peace he was solely responsible for the coalition that formed in order to discover Carthus. Nariin is unlike most nobles in the world as he makes judgement purely on merit rather than birth. Our intrepid heroes first encountered him in the docks of Sereni where he charged into a bandit hide-out and essentially kicked the crap out of everyone there with the help of Tharin and Juno.
Other than a distinct and divisive personality, the prince has a love of strong alcohol that nearly knocked out Tharin in a single gulp. A man after Tharin’s own heart, Alakh’s fighting style is similarly unique as it is powerful. Nariin boasts proficiency with all weapons and is able to summon a power from within to manipulate the wind in order to deliver a flurry of attacks. 
Our next encounter with the Prince was at dinner at the Bousant’s family home. The Bousant head, Argent Bousant had given sanctuary to both our intrepid heroes after being framed by the calculating Callidus Padron, and the Coalition Crew as Argent was Sereni’s minister for foreign affairs."

k3rYXjiEzK1H.title: Seko Shura
k3rYXjiEzK1H.content:
The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

"Our intrepid heroes first encountered the great Seko Shura unbeknownst to them outside the gates of Navlaan. He appeared as a homeless, one armed wanderer. Before their disagreement over the place of violence Shura even tutored Thomas after he survived execution at the hands of the paladins. Since then Seko was last seen as an escort to Devi his adopted niece, and trained Tharin in his Mountain Splitting technique.

In the Kolasi Archive Seko’s legend was uncovered: Seko killed the Gods by walking to the tallest mountain in Red Rock and cut in half to issue a challenge to them all. All the Gods, 1000 Gods, attacked at once. They all died in ten days, when Solaria and Tummora arrived. They wounded one another and called a stalemate. Seko blinded Tammora and blinded and ripped off Solaria's ears and she cut off his hand. Solaria wielded corruption in the battle.

When Thomas climbed the Black Mountain and met the Shadow Queen’s chief lieutenant Defiance, she alluded to the fact that Seko too had once climbed the same mountain. Thomas received a gift from Defiance but it is unclear what Seko received other than the disapproval of Defiance after he split her mountain."

DrnJJ8qelLsB.title: Juno Whitfoot
DrnJJ8qelLsB.content:
The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

"Juno is the nice guy of our Intrepid heroes, which is concerning because he’s a rogue. Juno is one of the original party members who met the party in Navlaan after stealing a weapon from a Four King’s barracks. Since then Juno has been a wanted man.

Juno earned the title “Giantslayer” during his time serving in the strike force sent to assassinate Varanoth outside Navlaan. Before the attack was planned the party visited Varanoth’s tower to ask Varanoth to resurrect Cooper who had been slain in a battle in Navlaan with invisible scouts. During his stay, Juno and Emmeline took part in a fighting pit and although Juno himself disputes the story (Juno and only Juno, everyone else agrees what happened), it was here Juno slew a giant in single combat. Since then his legend as the Giantslayer has been slowly growing throughout Carthus.

This however, was not the highlight of Juno’s stay as it was during this battle that Juno met the love of his life. A suited and booted tiefling, known simply as “The Announcer” who travels the world setting up fights such as these. Juno and the Announcer’s love story had only just begun in Navlaan but after also encountering him in Gromack, a few in the party suspect that Juno only travels with our heroes to have another shot at meeting the Announcer.

Like many in the party, Juno’s magnetic personality has attracted the patronage of a power being. Junos is a finely dressed man made of glass who acts as a Fence for Juno and his “reacquired goods."

ixecLlCf90Zp.title: Tharin
ixecLlCf90Zp.content:
The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

"Wherever Tharin goes, all NPCs hear is boss music (https://youtu.be/Aqk7x_w1H98). Tharin is one of our intrepid heroes, though only a fool would consider him a person or even a humanoid. The truth is Tharin is more of an embodiment of war, an individual that even the great Seko Shura looked upon and saw his potential for combat. Tharin joined the party in Navlaan though he originally hails from Gromack where he underwent the Ritual of Blood to become a Blood-Orc, a creature who lives to hunt the The Corruption. Since the ritual, Tharin is thought to be half-orc and half-elven. Tharin aspires to be the greatest warrior the world has ever seen, trying to master the wielding of two handed weapons in only a single hand he studies under Seko Shura and Khalisteth. From Shura he learns unbridled strength, the ability to cut entire buildings in half with a single strike at the cost of damage to himself. From Khalisteth he learns an insatiable thirst for battle, the ability to devour his opponents blood in order to fuel his abilities and even heal.
When our heroes visited Gromack, Tharin engaged a giant in single combat. Upon its defeat, he was accepted into the inner layers of Gromack and the upper-echelons of the blood clans. Shaman’s awarded him with a tattoo, a vision and a quest. Now Hellig had better watch out because Tharin’s looking for death, hunting the world’s strongest foes."
 

The following is from the notes of Juno Whitfoot:

“This fucker is terrifying. Note to self: do not anger this person.”

JWWaZZpIWk9M.title: Henry
JWWaZZpIWk9M.content:
The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

“Executioner Henry was at first, believed to be the replacement of Emmy as the Four King’s favoured Executioner. He was sent to hunt Emmy in Navlaan but wanted to reason with her instead. He offered Emmy a deal, perform one last execution and receive a pardon. Emmy instead ambushed him with the help of our Intrepid heroes which led to her kidnapping and a fortnight long chase across Carthus. Upon catching Henry not only was he prepared but he had slain his escort and any one else he met to create corpse piles all around his field of battle. He manipulated the spirits of the dead to battle the party and upon his defeat revealed himself to be reborn in flame as one of ten Solar Flares. Despite the party’s best efforts all but Thomas were felled with Juno even being outright killed. Rather than risk the lives of our heroes Thomas struck a bargain with Henry, their lives in return for giving one of the party up to Henry and the Kolasi (An ancient group who built archives beneath the ground). After Emmy resurrected Juno, the party decided to flee rather than honor the deal. They instead fled to Sereni.”
 

The following is from the notes of Juno Whitfoot:

“That asshole is nothing more than a flaming cunt with anger issues.”

YQDVx2dR2PFp.title: Devi
YQDVx2dR2PFp.content:
The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

“Devi is the adopted daughter of Ikor whom the party encountered in Navlaan when visiting the headquarters of Secretary Nailan. Devi is a young child who at first appeared human but who then healed Thomas of his corruption and revealed her ability to see it on those corrupted by it. Last the party saw of her, she was travelling with Seko back to her Father. As a gift from Thomas, she possesses the crown of the lost kingdom of Hestius, who refers to her as the Queen of Navlaan".

kUIdnJd2jeM0.title: Hellig (Mr Grim)
kUIdnJd2jeM0.content:
The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

"Mr Grim is the name given to the God of Death, Hellig by our author. Grim is a figure never encountered by the party, only by Thomas in his nightmares and research in the Kolasi archive. Grim’s intentions are unclear, only requesting to trial Thomas in return for power and the resurrection of Varanoth and the kingdom of Hestius. He appears to Thomas as a shadowy figure who constantly avoids been looked upon in an ocean of lost spirits and ravens.

Hellig’s legend is as follows:
There was a rebellion against titans (The Original Gods), by the son of the king of the titans, the God of death and a mortal (X is how he is referred). God of death created a spear to kill titans. He was the first person to kill titans but the rebellion failed and he was banished to the Plane of death, specifically for those who die horrible deaths. Hellig is Death’s name and X was imprisoned. Hellig is said to be the most powerful G-d and X was believed to be a mortal empowered with Hellig’s divinity to use as he saw fit."

hY6ew4mWd55j.title: Shadow Queen
hY6ew4mWd55j.content:
The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

“The Shadow Queen is a terrifying figure shrouded in mystery and darkness. Outside of Amara's personal experience (of which she keeps to herself) our Intrepid heroes only knowledge of there existence comes from the Kolasi archive. The only thing recorded, is that they seek to amass an army of loyal followers and has Defiance as her chief commander".

uYBj7cbAI0vf.title: Nailan
uYBj7cbAI0vf.content:
The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

“Former Secretary Nailan was the Paladin regent installed in Navlaan for a transition period. It was in this transition period that the party came to Navlaan and at first, in aiding Katherine were at odds with Nailan. This changed when the corrupted army marched on Navlaan and the party joined forces with Nailan and her militia to defend the town. 

Rather than risk the lives of her men in open combat, the party suggested a vanguard form and flank the army to defeat their leader. Nailan, Paladin’s Beno and Reece and the party assaulted Varanoth’s tower (Nailan had to stay behind to hold open the door) and successfully routed the corrupted army. 

Returning to Navlaan, Nailan expressed her resignation from her post and also her disillusionment with the Paladin Order. Before leaving Navlaan, Nailan was preparing to hand over her position to someone new from Sereni and was in the charge of Devi, who was staying in the third floor of the Paladin HQ that the party never got to explore (It was suspicious as hell though, no ways up to it aside from through Nailan’s room).”

Ey6sGOe4zQiT.title: Katherine
Ey6sGOe4zQiT.content:
Katherine was a primary school teacher in Navlaan before she had to flee the city before the Assault on Varanoth.

She became a target for the Paladins of Soliera after she was caught teaching anti-paladin topics and criticizing their regime, and the party was sent to track her down for her execution (though, they didn't know it). Once the party became aware of her situation they decided to help her flee the city instead of capturing her. While she was hiding under the Wanderer's Run and waiting to escape she became corrupted, giving her another reason to leave.

She ended up in Sereni, seemingly cured of her corruption. She was last seen in the basement of the Padron Family with Itzcoatl during the Fancy Funeral Fuckery.

The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

"Katherine… Katherine was the catalyst for the first adventure that our intrepid heroes partook in. In Navlaan, Katherine was a primary school teacher and harsh critic of the Paladin Regime there. These criticisms eventually culminated in Secretary Nailan producing a warrant for her arrest with the intent of public execution. Although this led to some disagreement in the party, our Handsome Author and Juno smuggled her out the city to safety after providing sanctuary in an old priest hole beneath Agroga's tavern. At the time, after a clash with invisible corrupted at her safe house, Katherine was corrupted and so intended to find a secluded trading caravan to take refuge in. Of course, anything involving Katherine could not be that simple.
The next encounter our intrepid heroes had with Katherine was in a middle-establishment tavern in Sereni, on a drunken night out after smuggling themselves into the nobles district under fake names. At 4 in the morning, a child of Defiance, whom Thomas had assigned to watch over Katherine, informed a hungover Thomas that Katherine had been kidnapped. A lengthy investigation ensued that led to the Padron crime family. Callidus himself informed the party that he indeed was holding Katherine in his basement and willingly parted this information. When the party arrived however, the party was ambushed by one of Itzcoatl’s abominations and Katherine was seen fleeing with the Surgeon after telling the party “This was the only way”, completely uncorrupted.
 

The following is from the notes of Juno Whitfoot:

"Honestly I still barely know fuck-all about Katherine, but Thomas seems to like her and I'm not one to let someone die because I don't know them. Also, I dropped 500 gold pieces on finding her and I'm not letting that money go to waste. 

One thing I will say is that she's got some balls on her, metaphorically speaking, and I can respect that. It takes courage to stand up to the paladins like she did, and in such a bold manner too. Not to mention she somehow lived through getting corrupted, though I imagine that was mostly Dr. Fuckface's doing. Not sure how though, she was already a human bloody scorpion in Navlaan and god-knows what she looked like by the time she got to Sereni."

loFnluurX9mT.title: Session 1
loFnluurX9mT.content:
The party from the start is: Cooper Brasskin, Emmy Crystalridge, Juno Whitfoot, Morradrith and Tharin.

Each of us for our own reasons enter into Navlaan. There are two paladin guards stationed outside manning the gate, and sitting next to the gate is a homeless man (Who we later learn is Seko Shura keeping an eye on Thomas).

We attend to our own business for some time, before we all converge on the Wanderer's Run, an Inn run by Agroga and her husband. Because this is dungeons and dragons we make quick friends in the Inn, booking rooms with each-other deciding to venture together. Juno shares a room with Morradrith, which he rapidly regrets.

aHfYlde933F1.title: Shih Xiezhi
aHfYlde933F1.content:
Shih Xiezhi is the first mate of the Iperos Coalition and princess of the Qian Kingdoms. She can be identified by her unique fashion sense, often wearing a stylish and easily identifiable red dress. Shih has the ability to ‘phase’ for lack of a better word: she has a knack for moving incredibly quickly and avoiding direct sight, as demonstrated by her observation of the party as they explored Sereni.

The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

"The Red Dressed Ghost has remained a mostly suspicious but ineffable figure to our intrepid heroes. They suspect she had been tailing them since they entered Sereni but at dinner at the Bousant’s she denied having left the compound".

Gn0KtzXKGGWl.title: Padron Family
Gn0KtzXKGGWl.content:
The Padrons are the wealthiest crime family in Sereni, matching only the merchant families in power. 

The ex-head of the family Astutus Padron recently died, leaving Callidus Padron as the head of the family.

Dwk9jHUXQvaE.title: Carthus
Dwk9jHUXQvaE.content:
Carthus is a continent that is almost entirely made up of a desert of black ash. The Kings of Sereni stake claim to this land, and while their legitimacy can be questioned their power cannot.

“One day, an mysterious force appeared, it infected everything from the tallest sky city to the deepest tunnel system. As it did so it warped and contaminated every living thing it touched. Vibrant forests began to twist and turn, trees that turn deep purple and sickly green. But worst of all were the monsters, any beast or monster that had existed was infected with this blight, it transformed these things into manifestations of their desires, fears and other such instincts. Not even man, and the other races that held civilisations were exempt from this, these two were warped with many turning into all kinds of monstrosities. Most of civilization was lost, damned to this infection. And so the paladins of Soliera stepped in, they purged the land of corruption through fire and light, burning away the land, the sky and everyone within it (the desolation event) creating what is now known as Carthus, the fields of ash. Whilst Carthus is nothing close to an ideal environment for life, the people there are free from corruption, and the tattered remains of the non corrupted paladins act as eternal sentries to protect from corruption.”

eyZ11PLr4l3G.title: Paladins of Soliera
eyZ11PLr4l3G.content:
The Paladins of Soliera are a semi-religious group in Carthus who are reportedly responsible for the 

“One day, an mysterious force appeared, it infected everything from the tallest sky city to the deepest tunnel system. As it did so it warped and contaminated every living thing it touched. Vibrant forests began to twist and turn, trees that turn deep purple and sickly green. But worst of all were the monsters, any beast or monster that had existed was infected with this blight, it transformed these things into manifestations of their desires, fears and other such instincts. Not even man, and the other races that held civilisations were exempt from this, these two were warped with many turning into all kinds of monstrosities. Most of civilization was lost, damned to this infection. And so the paladins of Soliera stepped in, they purged the land of corruption through fire and light, burning away the land, the sky and everyone within it (the desolation event) creating what is now known as Carthus, the fields of ash. Whilst Carthus is nothing close to an ideal environment for life, the people there are free from corruption, and the tattered remains of the non corrupted paladins act as eternal sentries to protect from corruption.”

SuvfpiQz3Kc0.title: Blood Orcs
SuvfpiQz3Kc0.content: "These orcs have undergone a trial of blood and ash and in the process become immune to the effects of The Corruption. However this comes at a cost, these Orcs crave blood like an addiction, specifically the blood of the corrupted. They often seek out the corrupted beasts within Carthus with some even venturing beyond the lands of Carthus into the corruptions domain."

nT172Y3GsslH.title: Knights of the four kings
nT172Y3GsslH.content: “The knights of the 4 kings are knights that serve the Kings of Sereni, (though the kings themselves claim to rule over all of Carthus.) These knights are divided into 4 divisions, 1 for each king and adopt fighting styles resembling the specific animal sigil that represents each king.”

IBFoGoSeN1Dd.title: Jade Panthers
IBFoGoSeN1Dd.content:
The Jade Panthers are one of the orders of the Knights of the four kings, specifically specializing in agile combat. They're well known for using stealth tactics rather than brute force.

“The Jade Panthers are dexterous predators, they believe in the kill and only the kill when it comes to fighting, often contrasting the Iron Bears, the panthers tend to prefer all manner of sneak attacks to take down their prey and avoid upfront confrontation when safer and more effective methods present themselves.”

Hw8yeYCb1lb1.title: Diamond Owls
Hw8yeYCb1lb1.content:
The Diamond Owls are one of the orders of the Knights of the four kings, specifically specializing in ranged fighting.

“The diamond Owl’s are scouts and ranged fighters, they prefer to take enemies at a distance and use their skills in archery or magic to win combat encounters. Though similar to the Iron bears they believe in honorable combat, and if necessary will fight up close if it is to preserve such honor. ”

2X2bhDuq1lsf.title: Iron Bears
2X2bhDuq1lsf.content:
The Iron Bears are one of the orders of the Knights of the four kings. They're stereotypical quite brutish and they prefer to use strength to come out on top in combat.

"The Iron bears are knights that represent the immovable object. They are hardy, often large in stature, and wield heavy armor, great shields and axes. They are known to be upfront fighters that don’t care for roundabout methods of assassination or sneak attacks. To them a strong fighter can withstand all manner of tricks without resorting to them. They are known to be a difficult group to handle for inn-keeps due to their more rowdy nature, but they are strong protectors."

Sppx5klvQRuv.title: Onyx Spiders
Sppx5klvQRuv.content:
The Onyx Spiders are one of the orders of the Knights of the four kings, specifically specializing in traps and schemes. They don't often resort to fighting, preferring to trade in espionage and information. 

“The Onyx spider never distinguishes themselves as such, nor are they knights by anything but name. They act more territorial, often watching over areas than travelling to encounters. These individuals tend to prefer laying carefully planned traps and schemes to neutralize threats. They also focus on gathering and extracting information over fighting skill. In their home territory they are the most dangerous of the knights to encounter but outside it they aren’t much stronger than a guard. ”

nL3YDR3bXVUF.title: Amygdala
nL3YDR3bXVUF.content:
“Bloodhunters are hunters of corruption, and in their fight against it they resort to all manner of strange and disturbing practices to warp one's body, soul and mind. Most bloodhunters don’t work as an organisation but instead work individually or in small groups. Often a child will be taken by a bloodhunter to be trained and then taken through the rituals, this means that there is great variation with how a bloodhunter fights, what kind of magic they use and what rituals they undergo. Whilst bloodhunters resist the corruption they are not immune to the effects and more recently have been corrupted blood hunters, who maintain the practice of taking an apprentice but whose goals are self-centred or for the sake of the corruption instead of against it. And the methods and rituals often infect the individual with the corruption to amplify strength

Additionally there is one organisation of bloodhunters known as Amygdala. This organisation operates both within and outside of Carthus with the goal of venturing into the corrupted lands and destroying the corruption for good. Their leader, Ludwig, is revered as a god by some townsfolk that rest on the border of the corrupted lands for his power and constant protection though anyone in Amygdala sees him as the leader and as the perfect bloodhunter that all should aim to become."

NnGNbpCh77eN.title: Callidus Padron
NnGNbpCh77eN.content:
Callidus Padron is the current head of the Padron crime family at a particularly young age. 

Callidus was the person who informed the party that Katherine was indeed being kept in the basement of the Padron family household during the Fancy Funeral Fuckery and led them down to it. However, this gesture was ultimately a trap to get the party arrested.

The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

“Callidus Padron is the leader of the most powerful crime family in Sereni, infamous for their red suits. Callidus was just 18 when the party met him at his Father’s, Astutus, funeral. He had a brief conversation with Thomas when revealed Katherine was being kept in his basement. After returning from the basement Callidus had called the King’s men and had the party arrested for breaking and entering.”
 

The following is from the notes of Juno Whitfoot:

"I've never met a criminal with so little integrity, except for maybe one kid who I watched steal a homeless bloke's blanket in Sereni. But, at least it could be argued that kid might have had a reason to do so, his elderly mother could have been dying of the cold or maybe the copper made from selling the rag would have bought food for the day. I'll never know the reason and it's harmful to speculate, everybody needs a little warmth sometimes, but my point is that you're able to speculate about his motivation at all.

Callidus would rip that sheet away from a hobo because it's an object that the fucker doesn't yet own, and from what I've seen he wont be content until he owns everything and everyone. I suppose that's what you get when so much power goes to the head of a rich bloke.

I wonder about that kid quite a bit nowadays. I hope people think about me the same way I do him, we all got reasons".

Q1ktQq2KNj6i.title: Sapientia Padron
Q1ktQq2KNj6i.content:
Sapientia Padron is the daughter of the late Astutus Padron, and member of the Padron crime family. 

She has incredible magical vision and is able to see through walls.

nRxB91ImJAns.title: Agroga
nRxB91ImJAns.content:
Agroga is the innkeep who owned and managed the Wanderer's Run with her husband, who was the chef. From what the party has seen she's a kind person with a good sense of humor and generosity.

Just before the Assault on Varanoth took place and the party was about to leave, Agroga realised that Navlaan was no-longer a safe place. She decided (perhaps mistakenly) to leave the keys of her inn to the party, essentially granting them ownership over the Wanderer's Run. She left the city soon after and traveled north to Sereni.

The following is from the notes of Juno Whitfoot:

“Agroga was proper nice to us, almost to a fault. I think over the two weeks we stayed there I only paid for one night, and then she gifted us the Inn anyway so it's not like it mattered. If we ever see her again I hope I'm not the one to tell her we trashed it beyond repair, I don't think I could take the shame”

WZebLgMT9dPu.title: Session 2
WZebLgMT9dPu.content:
While sleeping in the Wanderer's Run, Juno Whitfoot has a pretty shit dream. He dreams of a space made of shards of glass, within which is a man with slicked back hair in a dark trench-coat (who would come to be known as the Glass man). The glass man provides Juno with the ability to teleport a short distance. The glass man wants an orb of some kind, and wishes for Juno to steal it for him in return.

The next day, the party go into the desert to hunt a corrupted beast as a way of making money, since the Paladins of Soliera are paying those who hunt the corrupted. They are successful, and return to Navlaan to be paid a small amount.

fr0arfDdNGOC.title: Glass man
fr0arfDdNGOC.content:
The glass man is a being, perhaps an old god, who is the patron of Juno Whitfoot. According to Seko Shura, he's also able to shape-shift and isn't a person that should be easily trusted. Little else is known about this figure, although he almost certainly has ill intentions. 

Throughout the game the glass man has entrusted Juno with a variety of boons, including the ability to teleport short distances, limited spell-casting, and an orb which can transform into any instrument. He appears to reside in a dimension made up entirely of glass shards, which Juno is able to visit at will by using his ‘Gift of the void’ on any doorway.

aHmB2atiRFTS.title: Session 3
aHmB2atiRFTS.content:
The paladins ask us to find someone in the city who's been causing trouble named ‘Katherine’, although their reasons for asking are suspicious. Regardless, we agree to find this person and scour the city for them.

It turns out that Katherine is a school teacher who's been espousing anti-paladin values, and it's likely that the paladins wish to execute her. We decide that we can't let that happen and that she has a right to free speech, and so we tell her that she has to hide somewhere in the city, which she does.

While helping her escape, Juno Whitfoot and Morradrith are confronted by some paladin guards, which is where the session ends.

4Ytom1QZ7D0Y.title: Session 4
4Ytom1QZ7D0Y.content:
The session begins with Morradrith being captured by the paladin guards under suspicion of aiding a fugitive and he's taken to be interrogated. Juno manages to avoid this by simply running away. Katherine also escapes and hides in an empty building which is owned by her out-of-town friend.

The party re-convenes at the center of the town to discuss a way to break Morradrith out of ‘paladin jail’. To make sure that no-one is listening, Emmy casts detect magic and discovers that invisible feral goblins are listening in on the conversation. (We were very confused, and that's not how the spell works, but it's what happened). The party ignores the beasts for now, but we make sure they can't hear too much of our plans.

Half of the party decide to go and check on Katherine to make sure she hasn't been found but they run into another invisible goblin on the way which they decide to capture. While the party is talking, Morradrith is questioned and let go.

Sidenote, Emmy does some bullshit this session which I don't quite understand but it means she is able to get the casino coin.

6AtLfOJeOsSL.title: Session 5
6AtLfOJeOsSL.content:
People were away for this session, so it's quite short. We decided to play the session outside of the previous order of events, so Session 6 is the direct continuation of Session 4 instead of this one.

Ben decided to change characters, and so Morradrith left the party by disappearing into the sewers of Navlaan.

Juno attempts to look for where the invisible people are entering the city from and finds the secret entrance that they've been using.

XUmpoNNGmJh5.title: Session 6
XUmpoNNGmJh5.content:
Continuing from Session 4

Session 4 ended with Juno Whitfoot and Cooper Brasskin going to visit Katherine at her hiding place. Just before they knock on the door, a well dressed man carrying a large sword shows up and claims that he knows Katherine. This is Ben's new character Thomas Vic. 

Juno and Cooper talk with Thomas, initially being quite distrusting of him. Katherine lets all three of them inside her hideout and she does seem to know Thomas. The four of them chat, and while they chat the rest of the party show up.

Emmy Crystalridge once again checks for invisible creatures who could be listening in on the conversation and sees many of them surrounding the building. The party decide attack them in a fight which ends successfully for the party but does result in the death of Cooper.

A possessive presence takes control of the remaining invisible creature and talks through them. They says that they meant no harm to the party, they just wanted to keep watch on any influential people in Navlaan. They apparently have the power to resurrect creatures, and they offer to resurrect cooper if the party takes his body to their hideout Glasikov. The party agree, and begin the journey. Thomas joins the party, seemingly doing so to please Katherine.

aBKfBWXQ7u1b.title: Ludwig
aBKfBWXQ7u1b.content: The head of a group of blood-hunters in Redrock called the Amygdala. Not much is known about him other than the fact that he's revered by the local population because he strives to keep them free of corruption.

3dvwbrgmIfA9.title: Defiance
3dvwbrgmIfA9.content:
The following is from the notes of Thomas Vic:

"Defiance is an other worldly entity that serves as the Shadow Queen’s top lieutenant. They have yet to appear to our intrepid heroes as a group but has a long standing alliance with Thomas, despite the two’s opposing aims. Defiance’s grand plan is unclear but from their offers it is clear they hates tyrants and would love more than to see Thomas fall to their ideology of hate and rage.

Defiance has many children who take the form of black dragons in their lair atop the Black Mountain. Defiance themselves takes the form of a vorpal pit of darkness."
 

The following is from the notes of Juno Whitfoot:

“The fuck is that? No clue".

ertBsT6xfV2B.title: Session 7
ertBsT6xfV2B.content:
Brad's temporary character for the next few sessions is Ayryan Grey, but they're not particularly influential.

The party leave Navlaan and travel to Glasikov, a trip which takes a few days. On the way they meet two bloodhunters named Gallian and Sigaro from Redrock, the latter being the apprentice of the former.

One day while travelling in the glass plains, Tharin becomes enchanted by some magical force and travels to a tower in the desert. Most of the party decide to take a few days to look for him while Thomas takes the body of Cooper Brasskin to the location of the being who can resurrect him.

3703WSRXc4Yn.title: Session 8
3703WSRXc4Yn.content:
The party find Tharin in the tower, and in the tower they find a portal which leads to the location of Varanoth, arriving at the same time as Thomas Vic.

The party bargain with Varanoth for a long bloody time, which eventually results in Cooper being resurrected in return for luring the Paladins in Navlaan to a position where Varanoth can kill them easily. (Varanoth's main goal is to take over Navlaan and infect it with the corruption). With little choice, the party agree.

Ayryan Grey fucks off somewhere once Coopers is resurrected.

Yes, that conversation was the whole session :)

JG60IKvygeNS.title: Session 9
JG60IKvygeNS.content:
Two party memebers were missing for this session, and so this is the adventures of Cooper Brasskin, Juno Whitfoot and Emmy Crystalridge in the corrupted settlement. It's also the session.

The party leave Varanoth‘s tower into the settlement below. It’s a town make up entirely of corrupted, who seem to be much more like normal people than most other corrupted we've met. Juno buys a hat, and then Emmy and Juno decide to participate in a fighting tournament, which they barely win by killing a giant. A Tiefling simply called 'The Announcer‘ commentates the whole thing, and he’s incredible.

Using the money from winning Juno upgrades his rapier with a corrupted body part, calling it ‘Stinger’.

415Wj7PU3Q52.title: Session 10
415Wj7PU3Q52.content:
After some shopping, the party head back to Navlaan. It's an uneventful journey.

When they arrive at the gates of the city they realise that it's under quarantine because a corrupted person was spotted in the city a few days ago. We fruitlessly try to talk the guards into letting us past the gates but to no avail, until Thomas somehow gets secretary Nailan to come talk to us. They let us into the city once we tell them that we have information about a corrupted encampment nearby.
